    Constructs a st-dual graph Given a planar st-graph G, the dual planar st-graph G = (V, E) is a digraph with the following properties: - V* is the set of faces in G with the addition that the external face (s, . . . , t, . . . , s) is broken into two parts S* representing the portion of the face from s to t and T* representing the portion rom t to s. - For every edge e in E, we have an edge e* = (f, g) where f is the face the left of e and g is the face to the right of e.
